  "body": "Solidity supports the standard json setting `viaIR: true` to use the experimental Yul compilation pipeline (see https://docs.soliditylang.org/en/v0.8.6/using-the-compiler.html#compiler-input-and-output-json-description.)\r\n\r\nThe following is my hardhat config:\r\n\r\n```js\r\nmodule.exports = {\r\n  solidity: \"0.8.4\",\r\n  optimizer: {\r\n\t  enabled: true,\r\n\t  runs: 1000\r\n  },\r\n  viaIR: true\r\n};\r\n```\r\n\r\nAfter examining the standard json input from the contract artifact, there wwas no `viaIR: true` field in the input json.\r\n\r\nTo reproduce,\r\n\r\n1. `npx hardhat init`.\r\n2. Add the extra `viaIR: true` in hardhat config.\r\n\r\nAfter `npx hardhat compile`, notice that there is no `\"viaIR\": true` in the standard json input in `artifacts/build-info/*.json`.",
